    // — mirroring PauseTimer's own bookkeeping (record the reason, stash the full duration as the
    // remaining time) — rather than running for even one frame unpaused. Without this, a toast that
    // lands in an already-hovered/focused stack never gets its own PauseTimer(Group) call, because
    // OnExpandedChanged only fires on a genuine flip and Expanded is already true: it would count
